  {
    "@id": "https://ticketpro.ca/event/1689165018",
    "@type": [
      "http://schema.org/Event"
    ],
    "http://schema.org/startDate": [
      {
        "@type": "http://schema.org/Date",
        "@value": "2026-06-19T18:30:00-06:00"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/location": [
      {
        "@id": "https://ticketpro.ca/place/1300344751"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/image": [
      {
        "@id": "https://tprotom.ticketpro.ca/api/v1/resources/1692857368.jpeg?version=0"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/offers": [
      {
        "@id": "_:g1379300"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#wasDerivedFrom": [
      {
        "@id": "https://ww2.ticketpro.ca/event.php?event_id=7500"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/url": [
      {
        "@id": "https://ww2.ticketpro.ca/event.php?event_id=7500"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/name": [
      {
        "@value": "Morinville Festival Days Kickoff Dance Party"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/description": [
      {
        "@value": "<p>Get ready for a free dance party with live music, glowsticks, caricature artist, Hunter the Mascot, glitter tattoos and a paid snack concession. Grab your friend and hit the dance floor as The Oddibles bring the heat with a setlist spanning decades and genres—rock, pop, country, disco, Motown, and R&B. Don't miss the fun.  </p>\n\n \n\n<p><b>Tickets available starting May 19, 2026. </b></p>\n\n<p>Tickets* will be available to Morinville and Sturgeon County residents over the age of 16 from May 19 to 21, at the MCCC box office during operational hours. Proof of residency required. Tickets available to the general public online, in-person at the MCCC, and by phone, starting May 22 at 9 a.m. This is a free, ticketed event. Ticket required for everyone in attendance. Limit of 8 tickets per household. Please order only the tickets you will be using to ensure that everyone can enjoy this great family event.</p>\n\n \n\n<p>Children under the age of 13 must be accompanied by an adult. </p>\n\n \n\n<p>If you are unable to attend, physical tickets can be returned to the Morinville Community Cultural Centre before the event to be distributed to the waitlist. Online tickets can be returned via emailing <b>info@ticketpro.ca</b> and will be released back online and available for ordering.</p>\n<p>Tickets are free and have no cash value. Should the event sell out, you can check back here for online tickets that have been returned and/or be added to the waitlist by calling Community Services at 780-939-7839. For more information, please contact Community Services at 780-939-7839. </p>\n\n<p>Free parking is available at the Morinville Community Cultural Centre.<br>\nEvent activities subject to change without notice.<br>\n*While quantities last.</p>\n\n<style>\n.location-page-temp {\n    display: block!important;\n}\n</style>\n"
      }
    ],
