    ],
    "http://schema.org/name": [
      {
        "@value": "The Johner Brothers"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/description": [
      {
        "@value": "<p>In 1991, The Johner Brothers took the Canadian country music audience by storm. Brad and Ken were named 'Duo of the Year' by the Canadian Country Music Association, kicking off a string of awards. After being crowned 'Entertainer of the Decade' and releasing a remarkable 26 singles from six hit albums, Ken retired from the music business in 2002. Brad continued with a hugely successful solo career, recording six highly praised albums and awarded 'Male Artist of the Year' by the CCMA.</p>\n\n<p>After twenty years, the Johner Brothers are back together and looking forward to a busy year playing shows across western Canada. Backed by two of Brad's sons, the show is a fresh version of what Johner fans have come to expect as they are astute professionals and true gentlemen of the stage.</p>\n\n<p><a href='https://www.johnerbrothers.com/' target='_blank'><b>Website</b></a></p>\n\n<style>\n .location-page-temp {display: block!important;}\n</style>\n"
      }
