      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/name": [
      {
        "@value": "The Mudmen"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/description": [
      {
        "@value": "<p>A blast of Celtic energy is set to hit Drayton Valley when the Mudmen take to the stage! </p>\n\n<p>Blending bagpipes, drums, and a raucous spirit, their music is energizing and has become part of the Canadian soundtrack with over 3,000 live shows to date. In 2008, the Mudmen recorded the theme song for Hockey Night in Canada, solidifying their place as a quintessential part of Canada's pop culture.  </p>\n\n<p>Best described as an 'East Coast Kitchen Party - with electric guitars,' The Mudmen provide a truly unique, all-ages concert experience packed with Celtic music and stories. This band is described as Canada's Celtic Rock Warriors. Don't miss it!</p>\n\n<iframe width='560' height='315' src='https://www.youtube.com/embed/_argiO_tUfk?si=sT-gtA1i2CjvTUhX' title='YouTube video player' frameborder='0' allow='accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share' referrerpolicy='strict-origin-when-cross-origin' allowfullscreen></iframe>\n\n\n<style>\n@media screen and (max-width: 600px){iframe{width:100%;}}\n</style>\n"
      }
    ],
